{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The first half of the 20th century"},{"time":4000,"text":"was an absolute disaster in human affairs,"},{"time":7000,"text":"a cataclysm."},{"time":9000,"text":"We had the First World War,"},{"time":12000,"text":"the Great Depression,"},{"time":14000,"text":"the Second World War"},{"time":16000,"text":"and the rise of the communist nations."},{"time":19000,"text":"And each one of these forces"},{"time":21000,"text":"split the world, tore the world apart,"},{"time":23000,"text":"divided the world."},{"time":26000,"text":"And they threw up walls --"},{"time":28000,"text":"political walls, trade walls,"},{"time":30000,"text":"transportation walls,"},{"time":32000,"text":"communication walls, iron curtains --"},{"time":35000,"text":"which divided peoples and nations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39000,"text":"It was only in the second half of the 20th century"},{"time":43000,"text":"that we slowly began to pull ourselves"},{"time":46000,"text":"out of this abyss."},{"time":49000,"text":"Trade walls began to come tumbling down."},{"time":52000,"text":"Here are some data on tariffs:"},{"time":54000,"text":"starting at 40 percent, coming down to less than 5 percent."},{"time":57000,"text":"We globalized the world. And what does that mean?"},{"time":60000,"text":"It means that we extended cooperation"},{"time":63000,"text":"across national boundaries;"},{"time":65000,"text":"we made the world more cooperative."},{"time":68000,"text":"Transportation walls came tumbling down."},{"time":72000,"text":"You know in 1950 the typical ship carried"},{"time":75000,"text":"5,000 to 10,000 tons worth of goods."},{"time":79000,"text":"Today a container ship can carry 150,000 tons;"},{"time":83000,"text":"it can be manned with a smaller crew;"},{"time":85000,"text":"and unloaded faster than ever before."},{"time":88000,"text":"Communication walls, I don't have to tell you -- the Internet --"},{"time":91000,"text":"have come tumbling down."},{"time":93000,"text":"And of course the iron curtains,"},{"time":95000,"text":"political walls have come tumbling down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"Now all of this has been tremendous for the world."},{"time":103000,"text":"Trade has increased."},{"time":105000,"text":"Here is just a little bit of data."},{"time":107000,"text":"In 1990, exports from China to the United States:"},{"time":109000,"text":"15 billion dollars."},{"time":111000,"text":"By 2007: over 300 billion dollars."},{"time":115000,"text":"And perhaps most remarkably,"},{"time":118000,"text":"at the beginning of the 21st century,"},{"time":120000,"text":"really for the first time in modern history,"},{"time":124000,"text":"growth extended to almost all parts of the world."},{"time":128000,"text":"So China, I've already mentioned,"},{"time":130000,"text":"beginning around 1978, around the time of the death of Mao,"},{"time":133000,"text":"growth -- ten percent a year."},{"time":135000,"text":"Year after year after year,"},{"time":137000,"text":"absolutely incredible."},{"time":139000,"text":"Never before in human history"},{"time":143000,"text":"have so many people been raised out of"},{"time":145000,"text":"such great poverty as happened in China."},{"time":148000,"text":"China is the world's greatest anti-poverty program"},{"time":151000,"text":"over the last three decades."},{"time":153000,"text":"India, starting a little bit later,"},{"time":155000,"text":"but in 1990, begetting tremendous growth."},{"time":158000,"text":"Incomes at that time"},{"time":160000,"text":"less than $1,000 per year."},{"time":162000,"text":"And over the next 18 years"},{"time":164000,"text":"have almost tripled."},{"time":166000,"text":"Growth of six percent a year. Absolutely incredible."},{"time":169000,"text":"Now Africa, Sub-Saharan Africa --"},{"time":172000,"text":"Sub-Saharan Africa"},{"time":174000,"text":"has been the area of the world"},{"time":176000,"text":"most resistant to growth."},{"time":179000,"text":"And we can see the tragedy of Africa"},{"time":182000,"text":"in the first few bars here."},{"time":184000,"text":"Growth was negative."},{"time":186000,"text":"People were actually getting poorer than their parents,"},{"time":189000,"text":"and sometimes even poorer than their grandparents had been."},{"time":192000,"text":"But at the end of the 20th century,"},{"time":194000,"text":"the beginning of the 21st century,"},{"time":196000,"text":"we saw growth in Africa."},{"time":199000,"text":"And I think, as you'll see, there's reasons for optimism,"},{"time":201000,"text":"because I believe that the best is yet to come."},{"time":204000,"text":"Now why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206000,"text":"On the cutting edge today"},{"time":208000,"text":"it's new ideas which are driving growth."},{"time":210000,"text":"And by that I mean it's"},{"time":212000,"text":"products for which the research and development costs"},{"time":215000,"text":"are really high, and the manufacturing costs are low."},{"time":218000,"text":"More than ever before it is these types of ideas"},{"time":220000,"text":"which are driving growth on the cutting edge."},{"time":223000,"text":"Now ideas have this amazing property."},{"time":225000,"text":"Thomas Jefferson, I think, really expressed this quite well."},{"time":228000,"text":"He said, \"He who receives an idea from me"},{"time":232000,"text":"receives instruction himself, without lessening mine."},{"time":236000,"text":"As he who lights his candle at mine"},{"time":239000,"text":"receives light without darkening me.\""},{"time":242000,"text":"Or to put it slightly differently:"},{"time":244000,"text":"one apple feeds one man,"},{"time":246000,"text":"but an idea can feed the world."},{"time":249000,"text":"Now this is not new. This is practically not new to TEDsters."},{"time":252000,"text":"This is practically the model of TED."},{"time":254000,"text":"But what is new is that the greater function of ideas"},{"time":258000,"text":"is going to drive growth even more than ever before."},{"time":263000,"text":"This provides a reason why"},{"time":265000,"text":"trade and globalization"},{"time":267000,"text":"are even more important, more powerful than ever before,"},{"time":270000,"text":"and are going to increase growth more than ever before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273000,"text":"And to explain why this is so, I have a question."},{"time":276000,"text":"Suppose that there are two diseases:"},{"time":279000,"text":"one of them is rare, the other one is common,"},{"time":281000,"text":"but if they are not treated they are equally severe."},{"time":284000,"text":"If you had to choose, which would you rather have:"},{"time":287000,"text":"the common disease or the rare disease?"},{"time":291000,"text":"Common, the common -- I think that's absolutely right,"},{"time":293000,"text":"and why? Because there are more drugs to treat common diseases"},{"time":297000,"text":"than there are to treat rare diseases."},{"time":300000,"text":"The reason for this is incentives."},{"time":302000,"text":"It costs about the same to produce a new drug"},{"time":305000,"text":"whether that drug treats 1,000 people,"},{"time":308000,"text":"100,000 people, or a million people."},{"time":311000,"text":"But the revenues are much greater if the drug treats a million people."},{"time":314000,"text":"So the incentives are much larger"},{"time":317000,"text":"to produce drugs which treat more people."},{"time":321000,"text":"To put this differently: larger markets save lives."},{"time":325000,"text":"In this case misery truly does love company."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329000,"text":"Now think about the following:"},{"time":331000,"text":"if China and India were as rich as the United States is today,"},{"time":335000,"text":"the market for cancer drugs would be eight times larger than it is now."},{"time":341000,"text":"Now we are not there yet, but it is happening."},{"time":343000,"text":"As other countries become richer"},{"time":346000,"text":"the demand for these pharmaceuticals"},{"time":348000,"text":"is going to increase tremendously."},{"time":350000,"text":"And that means an increase incentive to do research and development,"},{"time":353000,"text":"which benefits everyone in the world."},{"time":356000,"text":"Larger markets increase the incentive"},{"time":358000,"text":"to produce all kinds of ideas,"},{"time":360000,"text":"whether it's software, whether it's a computer chip,"},{"time":362000,"text":"whether it's a new design."},{"time":364000,"text":"For the Hollywood people in the audience,"},{"time":366000,"text":"this even explains why action movies"},{"time":368000,"text":"have larger budgets than comedies:"},{"time":370000,"text":"it's because action movies translate easier"},{"time":373000,"text":"into other languages and other cultures,"},{"time":375000,"text":"so the market for those movies is larger."},{"time":377000,"text":"People are willing to invest more,"},{"time":379000,"text":"and the budgets are larger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381000,"text":"Alright. Well if larger markets increase the incentive"},{"time":384000,"text":"to produce new ideas,"},{"time":386000,"text":"how do we maximize that incentive?"},{"time":389000,"text":"It's by having one world market, by globalizing the world."},{"time":394000,"text":"The way I like to put this is:"},{"time":396000,"text":"one idea. Ideas are meant to be shared,"},{"time":399000,"text":"so one idea can serve one world, one market."},{"time":404000,"text":"One idea, one world, one market."},{"time":407000,"text":"Well how else can we create new ideas?"},{"time":410000,"text":"That's one reason."},{"time":412000,"text":"Globalize trade."},{"time":414000,"text":"How else can we create new ideas?"},{"time":416000,"text":"Well, more idea creators."},{"time":418000,"text":"Now idea creators, they come from all walks of life."},{"time":421000,"text":"Artists and innovators -- many of the people you've seen on this stage."},{"time":424000,"text":"I'm going to focus on scientists and engineers"},{"time":427000,"text":"because I have some data on that, and I'm a data person."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430000,"text":"Now, today, less than one-tenth of one percent"},{"time":435000,"text":"of the world's population are scientists and engineers."},{"time":438000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":440000,"text":"The United States has been an idea leader."},{"time":443000,"text":"A large fraction of those people are in the United States."},{"time":446000,"text":"But the U.S. is losing its idea leadership."},{"time":451000,"text":"And for that I am very grateful."},{"time":453000,"text":"That is a good thing."},{"time":456000,"text":"It is fortunate that we are becoming less of an idea leader"},{"time":459000,"text":"because for too long the United States,"},{"time":461000,"text":"and a handful of other developed countries,"},{"time":463000,"text":"have shouldered the entire burden"},{"time":465000,"text":"of research and development."},{"time":467000,"text":"But consider the following:"},{"time":470000,"text":"if the world as a whole were as wealthy as the United States is now"},{"time":473000,"text":"there would be more than five times as many scientists and engineers"},{"time":477000,"text":"contributing to ideas which benefit everyone,"},{"time":481000,"text":"which are shared by everyone."},{"time":483000,"text":"I think of the great Indian mathematician, Ramanujan."},{"time":487000,"text":"How many Ramanujans are there in India today"},{"time":491000,"text":"toiling in the fields, barely able to feed themselves,"},{"time":494000,"text":"when they could be feeding the world?"},{"time":497000,"text":"Now we're not there yet."},{"time":499000,"text":"But it is going to happen in this century."},{"time":502000,"text":"The real tragedy of the last century is this:"},{"time":508000,"text":"if you think about the world's population"},{"time":512000,"text":"as a giant computer, a massively parallel processor,"},{"time":515000,"text":"then the great tragedy has been"},{"time":517000,"text":"that billions of our processors have been off line."},{"time":522000,"text":"But in this century China is coming on line."},{"time":525000,"text":"India is coming on line."},{"time":527000,"text":"Africa is coming on line."},{"time":529000,"text":"We will see an Einstein in Africa in this century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534000,"text":"Here is just some data. This is China."},{"time":536000,"text":"1996: less than one million"},{"time":538000,"text":"new university students in China per year;"},{"time":541000,"text":"2006: over five million."},{"time":545000,"text":"Now think what this means."},{"time":547000,"text":"This means we all benefit when another country gets rich."},{"time":551000,"text":"We should not fear other countries becoming wealthy."},{"time":555000,"text":"That is something that we should embrace --"},{"time":558000,"text":"a wealthy China, a wealthy India, a wealthy Africa."},{"time":561000,"text":"We need a greater demand for ideas --"},{"time":563000,"text":"those larger markets I was talking about earlier --"},{"time":566000,"text":"and a greater supply of ideas for the world."},{"time":570000,"text":"Now you can see some of the reasons why I'm optimistic."},{"time":574000,"text":"Globalization is increasing the demand"},{"time":576000,"text":"for ideas, the incentive to create new ideas."},{"time":579000,"text":"Investments in education are increasing the supply of new ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"In fact if you look at world history"},{"time":587000,"text":"you can see some reasons for optimism."},{"time":589000,"text":"From about the beginnings of humanity"},{"time":591000,"text":"to 1500: zero economic growth, nothing."},{"time":594000,"text":"1500 to 1800: maybe a little bit of economic growth,"},{"time":598000,"text":"but less in a century"},{"time":600000,"text":"than you expect to see in a year today."},{"time":604000,"text":"1900s: maybe one percent."},{"time":606000,"text":"Twentieth century: a little bit over two percent."},{"time":608000,"text":"Twenty-first century could easily be 3.3, even higher percent."},{"time":612000,"text":"Even at that rate,"},{"time":614000,"text":"by 2100 average GDP per capita"},{"time":617000,"text":"in the world will be $200,000."},{"time":620000,"text":"That's not U.S. GDP per capita, which will be over a million,"},{"time":623000,"text":"but world GDP per capita -- $200,000."},{"time":626000,"text":"That's not that far."},{"time":628000,"text":"We won't make it."},{"time":630000,"text":"But some of our grandchildren probably will."},{"time":632000,"text":"And I should say,"},{"time":634000,"text":"I think this is a rather modest prediction."},{"time":637000,"text":"In Kurzweilian terms this is gloomy."},{"time":642000,"text":"In Kurzweilian terms I'm like the Eeyore of economic growth."},{"time":646000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":649000,"text":"Alright what about problems?"},{"time":651000,"text":"What about a great depression?"},{"time":654000,"text":"Well let's take a look. Let's take a look at the Great Depression."},{"time":658000,"text":"Here is GDP per capita"},{"time":660000,"text":"from 1900 to 1929."},{"time":663000,"text":"Now let's imagine that you were an economist in 1929,"},{"time":667000,"text":"trying to forecast future growth for the United States,"},{"time":670000,"text":"not knowing that the economy was about to go off a cliff,"},{"time":674000,"text":"not knowing that we were about to enter"},{"time":677000,"text":"the greatest economic disaster certainly in the 20th century."},{"time":681000,"text":"What would you have predicted, not knowing this?"},{"time":683000,"text":"If you had based your prediction, your forecast"},{"time":685000,"text":"on 1900 to 1929"},{"time":687000,"text":"you'd have predicted something like this."},{"time":689000,"text":"If you'd been a little more optimistic --"},{"time":691000,"text":"say, based upon the Roaring Twenties -- you'd have said this."},{"time":694000,"text":"So what actually happened?"},{"time":696000,"text":"We went off a cliff but we recovered."},{"time":700000,"text":"In fact in the second half of the 20th century"},{"time":703000,"text":"growth was even higher than anything you would have predicted"},{"time":707000,"text":"based upon the first half of the 20th century."},{"time":710000,"text":"So growth can wash away"},{"time":712000,"text":"even what appears to be a great depression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715000,"text":"Alright. What else?"},{"time":717000,"text":"Oil. Oil. This was a big topic."},{"time":720000,"text":"When I was writing up my notes oil was $140 per barrel."},{"time":727000,"text":"So people were asking a question. They were saying,"},{"time":730000,"text":"\"Is China drinking our milkshake?\""},{"time":734000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":735000,"text":"And there is some truth to this,"},{"time":738000,"text":"in the sense that we have something of a finite resource,"},{"time":742000,"text":"and increased growth is going to push up demand for that."},{"time":745000,"text":"But I think I don't have to tell this audience"},{"time":747000,"text":"that a higher price of oil is not necessarily a bad thing."},{"time":752000,"text":"Moreover, as everyone knows,"},{"time":755000,"text":"look -- it's energy, not oil, which counts."},{"time":758000,"text":"And higher oil prices mean"},{"time":760000,"text":"a greater incentive to invest in energy R&amp;D."},{"time":763000,"text":"You can see this in the data."},{"time":765000,"text":"As oil prices go up, energy patents go up."},{"time":768000,"text":"The world is much better equipped"},{"time":770000,"text":"to overcome an increase in the price of oil"},{"time":772000,"text":"today, than ever in the past,"},{"time":774000,"text":"because of what I'm talking about."},{"time":776000,"text":"One idea, one world, one market."}]},{"cues":[{"time":780000,"text":"So I'm optimistic"},{"time":783000,"text":"so long as we hew to these two ideas:"},{"time":785000,"text":"to keep globalizing world markets,"},{"time":787000,"text":"keep extending cooperation across national boundaries,"},{"time":791000,"text":"and keep investing in education."},{"time":794000,"text":"Now the United States has a particularly important role"},{"time":797000,"text":"to play in this:"},{"time":800000,"text":"to keep our education system globalized,"},{"time":803000,"text":"to keep our education system open to students from all over the world,"},{"time":807000,"text":"because our education system"},{"time":809000,"text":"is the candle"},{"time":811000,"text":"that other students come to light their own candles."},{"time":816000,"text":"Now remember here what Jefferson said."},{"time":819000,"text":"Jefferson said, \"When they come"},{"time":822000,"text":"and light their candles at ours,"},{"time":825000,"text":"they gain light, and we are not darkened.\""},{"time":830000,"text":"But Jefferson wasn't quite right, was he?"},{"time":833000,"text":"Because the truth is,"},{"time":836000,"text":"when they light their candles at ours,"},{"time":840000,"text":"there is twice as much light available for everyone."},{"time":844000,"text":"So my view is: Be optimistic."},{"time":848000,"text":"Spread the ideas. Spread the light."},{"time":851000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":853000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}